mdRecord.dcterms:creator: Murray, William Vans, 1760-1803
mdRecord.dcterms:description: Thanks him for letter; dreads of 19th article of treaty with the Dutch; error was on right side; difficulty of discharging general duties of neutrality will be great; ideas about restitution badly expressed; believed that Capt. Ferey would have his prize, he showing his commission.
